"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Examination.ID)\nFROM Examination\nJOIN Patient ON Examination.ID = Patient.ID\nWHERE Examination.Thrombosis = 1\n  AND YEAR(Examination.[Examination Date]) = 1997\n  AND Patient.SEX = 'F';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct female patients who had the most serious thrombosis cases examined in the year 1997. It joins the `Examination` and `Patient` tables using the foreign key relationship and applies the necessary filters based on the evidence provided."